    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains two time-aligned quantitative variables (temperature in \u00b0F, rainfall in mm) across 12 monthly categories. Synthetic data follows northern hemisphere seasonal patterns: temperature series (\u03bc=59.5, \u03c3=17.1) shows sinusoidal variation with summer peak, while rainfall (\u03bc=104.3, \u03c3=23.8) incorporates spring/summer convective maxima. Data ranges reflect temperate climate norms.\n\nThe dual-axis combination chart follows Tufte's principles by using distinct geometric encoding (line vs. column) for clear variable discrimination. Cairo's perceptual effectiveness is achieved through hue differentiation (blue=thermal, green=precipitation) and axis alignment. Spline smoothing emphasizes temperature trends while column bins highlight monthly rainfall totals. Secondary y-axis positioning prevents scale overlap while maintaining temporal alignment."
